---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import GalleryThumb from '~/components/GalleryThumb.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['generators']} city={cities['zeeland-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>Standby Power for Zeeland Homes, Farms, and Shops</h2>
    <p>
      Zeeland's mix of residential, agricultural, and light-manufacturing properties makes generator sizing a
      case-by-case job. A farm or shop has well pumps, ventilation, and motor loads that draw heavy startup current — a
      generator sized only for the running watts will stall the moment a motor kicks in. We account for those inrush
      loads in the calculation, not just the steady-state total.
    </p>
    <p>
      For working buildings, standby power is also tied to dedicated equipment circuits and reliable controls — see
      <a href="/electrical-repairs-zeeland-mi">electrical repairs in Zeeland</a> if your existing system needs attention
      first, or our <a href="/panel-upgrades-zeeland-mi">Zeeland panel upgrade page</a> if the service is undersized.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="container section-pad-tight">
    <h2>Recent Generator Work in Zeeland</h2>
    <div class="proof-grid">
      <figure class="proof-card">
        <GalleryThumb
          name="backup Generator"
          alt="Zeeland, MI Generac 22 kW natural gas whole-home standby generator installation"
          sizes="(max-width: 600px) 95vw, 50vw"
          width={400}
          height={300}
        />
        <figcaption>Zeeland — Generac 22 kW natural gas standby generator.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
